### Defining Components

Use `defineComponent` for type inference in Options API:

```js
import { defineComponent } from 'vue'

export default defineComponent({
  name: 'HelloWorld',
  data() {
    return { msg: 'Hello!' }
  }
})
```

### SFC Structure

A Single-File Component has three sections:

```vue
<template>
  <div class="example">
    <p>{{ greeting }}</p>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  data() {
    return { greeting: 'Hello from SFC!' }
  }
}
</script>

<style scoped>
.example p { color: blue; }
</style>
```

### Scoped Styles

When a `<style>` tag has the `scoped` attribute, its CSS applies only to the current component:

```vue
<style scoped>
/* Only affects this component's elements */
.title { font-size: 2em; }
</style>
```

Vue adds a unique attribute (like `data-v-xxxxx`) to elements and rewrites CSS selectors.

### Component Registration

**Global**: `app.component('MyComponent', MyComponent)` — available everywhere.

**Local**: Import and register in the `components` option:

```vue
<script>
import ChildComponent from './ChildComponent.vue'
export default {
  components: { ChildComponent }
}
</script>

<template>
  <ChildComponent />
</template>
```
